74-b13f-b81bdd064352\",\"version\":\"2.1.62\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/improve-agent-integration-skill\",\"slug\":\"vast-purring-aurora\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01ErD68qeCjXkFYYNGd9PrNV\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01ErD68qeCjXkFYYNGd9PrNV\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-28T00:31:17.981Z\",\"uuid\":\"22c94832-fd0a-4562-9dfc-89fd17206eed\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f0eb02fa-1b14-403b-850a-74b60e497f79\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"a97d7bdc-76ad-4774-b13f-b81bdd064352\",\"version\":\"2.1.62\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/improve-agent-integration-skill\",\"slug\":\"vast-purring-aurora\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01ErD68qeCjXkFYYNGd9PrNV\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1â†’# Implement Command\\n     2â†’\\n     3â†’Build the agent Go package using strict E2E-first TDD. Unit tests are written ONLY after all E2E tests pass.\\n     4â†’\\n     5â†’## Prerequisites\\n     6â†’\\n     7â†’- The research command's one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md`\\n     8â†’- The E2E test runner already added (from `write-tests` command)\\n     9â†’- If no one-pager exists, read the agent's docs and ask the user about hook events, transcript format, and config\\n    10â†’\\n    11â†’## Core Principle: E2E-First TDD\\n    12â†’\\n    13â†’1. **E2E tests are the spec.** The existing `ForEachAgent` test scenarios define \\\"working\\\". You implement until they pass.\\n    14â†’2. **Watch it fail first.** Every E2E tier starts by running the test and observing the failure. If you haven't seen the failure, you don't understand what needs fixing.\\n    15â†’3. **Minimum viable fix.** At each failure, implement only the code needed to make that specific assertion pass. Don't anticipate future tiers.\\n    16â†’4. **`/debug-e2e` is your debugger.** When an E2E test fails, use the artifact directory with `/debug-e2e` before guessing at fixes.\\n    17â†’5. **No unit tests during Steps 4-13.** Unit tests are written in Step 14 after all E2E tiers pass, using real data from E2E runs as golden fixtures.\\n    18â†’6. **Format and lint, don't unit test.** Between E2E tiers, run `mise run fmt && mise run lint` to keep code clean. No `mise run test` until Step 14.\\n    19â†’7. **If you didn't watch it fail, you don't know if it tests the right thing.**\\n    20â†’\\n    21â†’**Do NOT write unit tests during Steps 4-13.** All test writing is consolidated in Step 14.\\n    22â†’\\n    23â†’## Procedure\\n    24â†’\\n    25â†’### Step 1: Read Implementation Guide\\n    26â†’\\n    27â†’Read these files thoroughly before writing any code:\\n    28â†’\\n    29â†’1. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` â€” Authoritative implementation guide with code templates. Read thoroughly.\\n    30â†’2. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` â€” Validation criteria for completeness.\\n    31â†’3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` â€” Read to find the exact `Agent` interface and all optional interfaces.\\n    32â†’4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` â€” Read to find `EventType` constants and shared parsing helpers.\\n    33â†’\\n    34â†’### Step 2: Read Reference Implementation\\n    35â†’\\n    36â†’Read `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md` (the one-pager from the research phase) for the agent's hook mechanism, transcript format, and config structure.\\n    37â†’\\n    38â†’Run `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")` to find all existing agent packages. Check the one-pager's \\\"Hook Mechanism\\\" and \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" sections to pick the best reference â€” choose an agent with a similar hook mechanism to your target. Read all `*.go` files (skip `*_test.go` on first pass) in the chosen reference.\\n    39â†’\\n    40â†’### Step 3: Create Bare-Minimum Compiling Package\\n    41â†’\\n    42â†’Create the agent package directory and stub out every required interface method so the project compiles.\\n    43â†’\\n    44â†’```\\n    45â†’cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/\\n    46â†’```\\n    47â†’\\n    48â†’**What to create:**\\n    49â†’\\n    50â†’1. **`${AGENT_PACKAGE}.go`** â€” Struct definition, `init()` with `agent.Register(agent.AgentName(\\\"$AGENT_KEY\\\"), New)`, and stub implementations for every method in the `Agent` interface â€” refer to `agent.go` from Step 1. Include `HookSupport` methods in `lifecycle.go` and `hooks.go`.\\n    51â†’2. **`types.go`** â€” Hook input struct(s) with JSON tags matching the one-pager's \\\"Hook input (stdin JSON)\\\" section.\\n    52â†’3. **`lifecycle.go`** â€” Stub `ParseHookEvent()` that returns `nil, nil` for all inputs. Use the one-pager's \\\"Hook names\\\" table for the native hook name â†’ Entire EventType mapping.\\n    53â†’4. **`hooks.go`** â€” Stub `InstallHooks()`, `UninstallHooks()`, `AreHooksInstalled()` that return nil/false. Use the one-pager's \\\"Config file\\\" and \\\"Hook registration\\\" sections for the config path and format.\\n    54â†’5. **`transcript.go`** â€” Stub `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods if the one-pager's \\\"Transcript\\\" section indicates the agent supports transcript analysis. Use the one-pager for transcript location and format.\\n    55â†’\\n    56â†’**Wire up blank imports:**\\n    57â†’\\n    58â†’- Ensure the blank import `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE\\\"` exists in `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`\\n    59â†’\\n    60â†’**Verify compilation:**\\n    61â†’\\n    62â†’```bash\\n    63â†’mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test\\n    64â†’```\\n    65â†’\\n    66â†’Everything must pass before proceeding. Fix any issues.\\n    67â†’\\n    68â†’**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n    69â†’\\n    70â†’**Standing instruction for Steps 4-12:** If you need agent-specific information (hook format, transcript location, config structure), check `AGENT.md` first. If `AGENT.md` doesn't cover what you need, you may search external docs â€” but always update `AGENT.md` with anything new you discover so future steps don't need to re-search.\\n    71â†’\\n    72â†’### Step 4: E2E Tier 1 â€” `TestHumanOnlyChangesAndCommits`\\n    73â†’\\n    74â†’This test requires no agent prompts â€” it only exercises hooks, so it's the fastest feedback loop.\\n    75â†’\\n    76â†’**What it exercises:**\\n    77â†’- `InstallHooks()` â€” real hook installation in the agent's config\\n    78â†’- `AreHooksInstalled()` â€” detection that hooks are present\\n    79â†’- `ParseHookEvent()` â€” at minimum, the event types needed for session start and turn end (see `EventType` constants in `event.go`)\\n    80â†’- Basic hook invocation flow (the test calls hooks directly via the CLI)\\n    81â†’\\n    82â†’**Cycle:**\\n    83â†’\\n    84â†’1. Run: `mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG TestHumanOnlyChangesAndCommits`\\n    85â†’2. **Watch it fail** â€” read the failure output carefully\\n    86â†’3. If there are artifact dirs, use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` to understand what happened\\n    87â†’4. Implement the minimum code to fix the first failure\\n    88â†’5. Repeat until the test passes\\n    89â†’\\n    90â†’Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n    91â†’\\n    92â†’**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n    93â†’\\n    94â†’### Step 5: E2E Tier 2 â€” `TestSingleSessionManualCommit`\\n    95â†’\\n    96â†’The foundational test. This exercises the full agent lifecycle: start session â†’ agent prompt â†’ agent produces files â†’ user commits â†’ session ends.\\n    97â†’\\n    98â†’**What it exercises:**\\n    99â†’- Complete `ParseHookEvent()` for all lifecycle event types from `event.go`. Use the one-pager's hook mapping table to translate native hook names to `EventType` constants.\\n   100â†’- `Get